00:31:34.530 --> 00:31:36.429
All right, so that's PWAs.

00:31:36.429 --> 00:31:38.220
The second initiative
I want to talk to you

00:31:38.220 --> 00:31:42.840
about is called
Accelerated Mobile Pages.

00:31:42.840 --> 00:31:45.720
We just call it AMP for short.

00:31:45.720 --> 00:31:48.900
And while PWA was
about expanding

00:31:48.900 --> 00:31:51.630
the capabilities
of web browsers,

00:31:51.630 --> 00:31:54.450
AMP is really more
about streamlining

00:31:54.450 --> 00:31:56.340
what we do with
the web to deliver

00:31:56.340 --> 00:32:03.630
a trimmed down, open source web
format that loads instantly.

00:32:03.630 --> 00:32:07.500
It works by defining
a subset of HTML

00:32:07.500 --> 00:32:12.270
and using web
components to create

00:32:12.270 --> 00:32:17.370
a set of HTML that loads
without blocking on any network

00:32:17.370 --> 00:32:18.610
resources.

00:32:18.610 --> 00:32:22.380
So it shows up instantly, and
the images and JavaScript load

00:32:22.380 --> 00:32:26.820
asynchronously, and you're
guaranteed when you use AMP

00:32:26.820 --> 00:32:29.160
that none of these
resources, as they load,

00:32:29.160 --> 00:32:33.210
will cause the web page
to have to repaint itself.

00:32:33.210 --> 00:32:35.952
We call it a reflow when it
has to lay itself out again

00:32:35.952 --> 00:32:37.410
because something
that's loaded has

00:32:37.410 --> 00:32:40.320
caused it to change its layout.

00:32:40.320 --> 00:32:43.620
As a result, these things
create just a really fast, fast,

00:32:43.620 --> 00:32:47.510
fast experience
that pulls users in.

00:32:47.510 --> 00:32:50.960
We found that over
700,000 domains are now

00:32:50.960 --> 00:32:54.200
serving at least
AMPed page, and it's

00:32:54.200 --> 00:32:58.130
compatible with more than 70 eds
and analytic solutions, which

00:32:58.130 --> 00:32:59.930
are important as you
monetize and measure

00:32:59.930 --> 00:33:03.230
what's happening on your site.

00:33:03.230 --> 00:33:08.630
Many popular web platforms like
WordPress, Drupal, Squarespace,

00:33:08.630 --> 00:33:12.440
and Shopify, have integrated
AMP into their platforms, which

00:33:12.440 --> 00:33:15.290
makes it super easy for
you to take your content

00:33:15.290 --> 00:33:18.260
and make it AMP compatible.

00:33:18.260 --> 00:33:21.500
And these are just web pages,
so anyone can host them.

00:33:21.500 --> 00:33:24.770
But we've created something
called the Google AMP

00:33:24.770 --> 00:33:27.850
Cache, which is a
free, global caching

00:33:27.850 --> 00:33:30.980
service for all AMP content.

00:33:30.980 --> 00:33:32.930
Anyone can use this
thing, and it's

00:33:32.930 --> 00:33:35.890
another one of the ingredients
that makes AMP really fast,

00:33:35.890 --> 00:33:38.650
because when they're
hosted with this cache,

00:33:38.650 --> 00:33:42.410
pages load even faster than if
users pull them from the origin

00:33:42.410 --> 00:33:42.910
servers.

00:33:45.500 --> 00:33:48.200
We're seeing a lot of industry
adoption of AMP pages,

00:33:48.200 --> 00:33:51.020
with sites like Bing,
Twitter, Pinterest,

00:33:51.020 --> 00:33:53.930
and of course our own Google
Search linking to AMP pages

00:33:53.930 --> 00:33:58.950
and using the AMP
cash when available.

00:33:58.950 --> 00:34:01.520
We're also continuing
to evolve AMP.

00:34:01.520 --> 00:34:04.420
We're working with e-commerce
companies such as eBay

00:34:04.420 --> 00:34:07.330
to take what we've done and
to expand its capabilities

00:34:07.330 --> 00:34:11.514
to work even better in
domains like e-commerce.

00:34:11.514 --> 00:34:12.889
And one of my
favorite sayings is

00:34:12.889 --> 00:34:16.219
that we've integrated
AMP and PWAs together

00:34:16.219 --> 00:34:18.170
which, when you think
about it, is a pretty

00:34:18.170 --> 00:34:20.570
compelling combination.

00:34:20.570 --> 00:34:25.389
Because with AMP we can serve
a page instantly to users,

00:34:25.389 --> 00:34:29.139
super fast, and then while
users are browsing that content,

00:34:29.139 --> 00:34:31.699
we can load a PWA
in the background

00:34:31.699 --> 00:34:35.719
and users can then convert
from the end page to the PWA

00:34:35.719 --> 00:34:38.460
and have a rich,
interactive experience.

00:34:38.460 --> 00:34:41.810
It's a great way to
keep your users engaged.

00:34:41.810 --> 00:34:44.631
All right, so that's what
we're doing with the web.

